<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870330-0156 </DOCNO><HL> Corning Buys Stake in Firm</HL><DD> 03/30/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GLWTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> CORNING, N.Y.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Corning Glass Works said it bought a 50% stake in closely held Technology Dynamics Inc., Woodinville, Wash. Terms weren't disclosed.    Technology Dynamics researches and develops fiber-optic sensors for process control, semiconductor, aircraft, electric power, industrial machine, and medical instrumentation markets. Corning is a specialty glass and ceramics, consumer housewares and telecommunications concern. </TEXT></DOC>